Package: rieszboost
Type: Package
Title: Gradient Boosting for Riesz Representers
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(person("Alejandro", "Schuler", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                    email = "aschuler@berkeley.edu"))
Description: R wrapper around the Python rieszboost library implementing
    Lee & Schuler (2025) RieszBoost. Provides direct estimation of Riesz
    representers for linear functionals of conditional expectations, used
    in semiparametric estimation (ATE, ATT, treatment-specific means,
    shift interventions). Computation is delegated to the Python package
    via reticulate.
License: TBD
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    R6,
    reticulate (>= 1.30),
    rieszreg (>= 0.0.1)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    pkgload
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.10), the Python package 'rieszboost'
RoxygenNote: 7.3.0
